1. What is EDA?
"Data ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§ï‡§π‡§æ‡§®‡•Ä ‡§∏‡§Æ‡§ù‡§®‡•á ‡§ï‡§æ ‡§§‡§∞‡•Ä‡§ï‡§æ"

Goal: Find patterns, errors, and relationships before modeling.

2. Why EDA? (Need)
Data ‡§∏‡§Æ‡§ù‡•ã ‚Üí Missing values, outliers, distributions.

Model ‡§ï‡•Ä performance ‡§¨‡§¢‡§º‡§æ‡§ì (Better features = Better predictions).

Wrong assumptions ‚Üí Wrong results (EDA fixes this).

3. History (Short)
1977: John Tukey (Statistician) coined term "EDA".

Pre-ML Era: Used in stats (mean, median, plots).

Modern ML: Automated EDA (Pandas-profiling, Sweetviz).

4. Types of EDA (Simple)
Univariate ‚Üí 1 variable (e.g., Bitcoin price distribution).

Bivariate ‚Üí 2 variables (e.g., Price vs Volume correlation).

Multivariate ‚Üí 3+ variables (e.g., Heatmaps, PCA).
